<h2 id="how-to-master-difficult-pinky-stretches-with-d-major">How to master difficult pinky stretches with D-major</h2>

<p>It is relatively common, when using a D-major chord, to have a song require you to put a finger down on the 4th fret of either the 3rd or 4th string. In this lesson, Iâ€™ll explain how to go about practicing this technique - because it isnâ€™t easy at first!</p>

<h2 id="understanding-the-chord-shapes">Understanding the chord shapes</h2>

<p>First, let us start with the normal D-chord which you probably know. Even when you later on add your pinky, itâ€™s important to know - the 3 fingers shown here should always stay in these positions!</p>

